<td>Vendor content, peer recommendations, webinars</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Supplier evaluation</td>
<td>Case studies, demos, pricing pages, references</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Purchase decision</td>
<td>Sales calls, proposals, procurement processes</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></div>
<p><strong>Key insight:</strong> Vendor websites and organic content are the primary research channels for the middle and late stages. If your site does not answer the questions buyers ask at each stage, they move to competitors.</p>
